        "text": "The place that never saw sunset has been claimed by the sea, and yet the darkness that once imprisoned this isle now glows before me, vibrant and alive.\n\nIf this resurrection has nothing to do with her longing, then how did she reclaim life itself?\n\nRegina once spoke of her past with Albrecht—colleagues bound by their knowledge of Alchemy's deepest mysteries.\n\nBlood carries memory in its crimson depths. Perhaps Albrecht drew upon Regina's essence to grant her new life within The Exodus.\n\nI wrote seeking answers, but his reply was simply a blank parchment and silence.",
